Company Description Progress Rail, a Caterpillar company, is an integrated rolling stock and infrastructure provider, delivering a full range of products and services to domestic and international railroad customers. Our customers enjoy one-stop shopping and comprehensive cradle-to-grave railway solutions - whether it rolls on the rail or is the rail itself. From locomotives, transit, freight cars and engines, to tracks, signals and advanced technology, we ensure customers can count on us to meet all their rail needs. Forging the bridge between ideas and success, our talented and innovative team members work together to address the challenges of the rail industry today, ensuring success for the future. As part of a vibrant, global network of business operations, each and every member of our team is important to our success. With headquarters in Albertville, Ala., more than 7,000 dedicated employees serve customers through a network of close to 150 locations around the world. For more information, visit www.progressrail.com and follow @Progress_Rail on Twitter and YouTube.

Job Purpose Progress Rail Services Corporation, a Caterpillar Company and a leading provider of services to the Railroad industry in the US, Canada, Mexico, and Brazil, seeks a Software Engineer at our facility in Independence, MO.

The successful candidate is responsible for Windows and embedded software application solutions for our Carborne Event Recorder product line. This position will works closely with product management and engineering in requirements gathering and software design and development. Organizational skills and the ability to multi-task in a fast paced environment are a must.

Key Job Elements • Coordinating and defining requirements and application design from product management and field engineering;
Development, testing and deployment of product executive software in a Windows based development environment;
Managing the development of product & software documentation;
Software configuration management and workflows;
Troubleshoot remote hardware and software issues.
Education / Training • Bachelor’s Degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering or Computer Science required.

Qualifications and Experience • 3 to 5 years’ experience in a Windows/10 software development environment and/or a QNX/Linux development environment;
Knowledge of C++, C#, .NET, SQL, and database management tools;
Experience in Visual Studio required;
Candidate must have initiative and a driven, high-performance work ethic;
Candidate must work well in a high-energy team environment;
Solid communication skills.
Benefits Progress Rail Services Corporation and its subsidiary and affiliate companies offer an excellent total compensation package* including competitive salary, 401(k) plan with company match, available medical/dental/life/disability insurance coverage and paid vacation and holidays. Relocation assistance may be available for some positions.
